criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients are eligible if aged between 25 and 65 years, have a body mass index of 35
             (in presence of complications as sleep apnea, severe coxarthritis or gonarthritis,
             severe hypertension) to 50 kg/m2, and are able to understand and comply with the study
             process.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  History of type 1 diabetes or secondary diabetes;

          -  Previous bariatric surgery;

          -  History of medical problems such as mental impairment;

          -  Major cardiovascular disease;

          -  Major gastrointestinal disease;

          -  Major respiratory disease;

          -  Hormonal disorders;

          -  Infection;

          -  History of drug addiction and/or alcohol abuse;

          -  Internal malignancy;

          -  Pregnancy;

          -  Impaired glucose tolerance;

          -  Suspected or confirmed poor compliance;

          -  Informed consents.
